1. Deceit is, When ſouls reſt ſatisfied with ſomething that's like it, and yet at that time, and alſo before, never paſſed under, or know what it is to be inriched with the nature of the thing: as thus;

Becauſe Converſion is a change, therefore any change; becauſe it's a turning, therefore any turning; becauſe it's light, therefore any light; and becauſe there is life and joy, therefore if any, it muſt be that.

Here was the young man in the Goſpel deceived, Mat. 19, 20. And ſo the Phariſes, Luke 18.11, 12. And ſo at the laſt day, Mat. 7.22.

                  Doct. 3. It is not only propper to, but the Priviledge of Humble Souls to bleſs, or rejoyce in God's Goodneſs to particular Saints, or Zion in general.



                        All was reduced to one Doctrine;


The rejoycing at, or in the Goodneſs of God to particular Saints, eſpecially upon Zions account, is a Priviledge and Imployment proper only to Humble Souls.
